Input parquet files go in ./sharded/
Result gets saved to ./output/
About 3k sentences take < 20h on A100

./deploy.sh creates the environment, and downloads the models and code
./run_all.sh creates a job.sbatch file for all input files
sbatch job.sbatch lanches the job array

Examples:
srun -A fev@a100 --partition=compil --cpus-per-task=10 --hint=nomultithread ./deploy.sh
srun -A fev@a100 --partition=gpu_p5 -C a100 --gres=gpu:1 --hint=nomultithread --cpus-per-task=16 ./run_one.sh sharded/text_data_00000000.parquet output/text_data_00000000.parquet

